==English==
{{wikipediapar|Sore}}

===Pronunciation===
*sô(r), /soʊr/, /sɔː(r)/, /<tt>sO:(r)</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[soar]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɔː(r)|Rhymes: -ɔː(r)]]

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[sār]]''

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|sor|er|est}}

# Causing [[pain]] or [[discomfort]]; [[painful]]ly [[sensitive]].
#:''Her feet were '''sore''' from walking so far.''
# Feeling animosity towards; [[annoyed]] or [[angered]].
#:''Joe was '''sore''' at Bob for beating him at checkers.''
# [[dire|Dire]]; [[distress]]ing.
#:''The school was in [[sore]] need of textbooks, theirs having been ruined in the flood.''

