===Adverb===
{{en-adv}}

# {{archaic}} [[sorely|Sorely]].
#*'''1919:''' Edgar Rice Burroughs, ''Jungle Tales of Tarzan'' [http://etext.lib.virginia.edu/etcbin/ot2www-pubeng?specfile=/texts/english/modeng/publicsearch/modengpub.o2w&act=surround&offset=119320172&tag=Burroughs,+Edgar+Rice,+1875-1950:+Jungle+Tales+of+Tarzan,+1919&query=+sore+pressed&id=BurJung]
#*:...[they] were often '''sore''' pressed to follow the trail at all, and at best were so delayed that in the afternoon of the second day, they still had not overhauled the fugitive.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#An [[injured]], [[infected]], [[inflamed]] or [[diseased]] patch of [[skin]].
#:''They put ointment and a bandage on the '''sore'''.''

